From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 03 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] egl: add DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID to render formats unconditionally

PowerVR DDK 24.x reports all explicit modifiers as external_only=true,
so the original condition (modifiers_len==0 || !all_external_only) never
adds DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID to dmabuf_render_formats.  This leaves the
render format set empty, causing every wlroots format check to fail with
"Renderer doesn't support format".

Add INVALID unconditionally — the driver can still render with implicit
modifiers even when all explicit modifiers are external-only.  Also add
LINEAR unconditionally when modifiers_len==0 (driver doesn't advertise
modifiers), consistent with the original intent for modifier-less drivers.

---
 render/egl.c | 18 +++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/render/egl.c b/render/egl.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/render/egl.c
+++ b/render/egl.c
@@ -134,23 +134,19 @@ static void egl_init_formats(struct wlr_egl *egl) {
 		has_modifiers = has_modifiers || modifiers_len > 0;

-		bool all_external_only = true;
 		for (int j = 0; j < modifiers_len; j++) {
 			wlr_drm_format_set_add(&egl->dmabuf_texture_formats, fmt,
 				modifiers[j]);
 			if (!external_only[j]) {
 				wlr_drm_format_set_add(&egl->dmabuf_render_formats, fmt,
 					modifiers[j]);
-				all_external_only = false;
 			}
 		}

-		// EGL always supports implicit modifiers. If at least one modifier supports rendering,
-		// assume the implicit modifier supports rendering too.
+		// EGL always supports implicit modifiers. Add INVALID unconditionally —
+		// even when all explicit modifiers are external-only (e.g. PVR DDK 24.x),
+		// the driver can still render with implicit modifiers.
 		wlr_drm_format_set_add(&egl->dmabuf_texture_formats, fmt,
 			DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID);
-		if (modifiers_len == 0 || !all_external_only) {
-			wlr_drm_format_set_add(&egl->dmabuf_render_formats, fmt,
-				DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID);
-		}
+		wlr_drm_format_set_add(&egl->dmabuf_render_formats, fmt,
+			DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID);

 		if (modifiers_len == 0) {
 			// Assume the linear layout is supported if the driver doesn't
